decks.notes: The deck focuses on aggressive creatures with powerful abilities, supported by a range of multicolored spells and lands. The goal is to quickly apply pressure to the opponent and close out the game before they have a chance to stabilize. By utilizing efficient creatures like Wild Nacatl and Ragavan, Nimble Pilferer, alongside powerful spells like Lightning Bolt and Tribal Flames, the deck aims to overwhelm the opponent with a fast and aggressive strategy. Leyline Binding and Stubborn Denial provide some disruption and protection, allowing the deck to maintain its aggressive momentum.

This deck aims to disrupt the opponent's game plan while putting pressure on them with aggressive creatures. It focuses on efficient removal and hand disruption to control the board, while also utilizing cards that benefit from flickering and sacrificing creatures. The deck includes a mix of low-cost creatures to apply early pressure and higher-cost creatures with powerful abilities to close out the game. It aims to outvalue the opponent by leveraging its synergies and disruptive elements to gain incremental advantages and win the game.

The deck revolves around cycle creatures and using spells to control the board until the combo pieces are assembled. The goal is to fill the graveyard with creatures and then cast Living End to bring them all back onto the battlefield, overwhelming the opponent with a massive army. The deck includes counter magic and disruptive spells to protect the combo and disrupt the opponent's game plan. The creatures in the deck are chosen specifically to work well with the Living End mechanic, providing value when they enter the battlefield. The deck aims to win quickly once the combo is assembled.

The deck focuses on leveraging the powerful combo potential of Allosaurus Rider alongside cards like Neoform and Eldritch Evolution to quickly assemble a game-winning board state. By tutoring for key pieces with cards like Eladamri's Call and Summoner's Pact, the deck can efficiently set up its combo while also ramping into big threats like Ghalta, Stampede Tyrant and Terastodon. The inclusion of Planar Genesis helps to accelerate the deck's mana production, allowing for explosive turns that can overwhelm opponents. With a mix of creature-based combo pieces and strong support cards, this deck aims to quickly dominate the battlefield and secure victory.

This Boros Aggro deck aims to overwhelm the opponent with a combination of early aggressive creatures like Guide of Souls and Ragavan, Nimble Pilferer, backed up by powerful spells like Ajani, Nacatl Pariah and Galvanic Discharge. The deck also includes disruptive elements like Static Prison and Ranger-Captain of Eos to control the board and protect its threats. With a mix of efficient creatures, removal spells, and versatile enchantments, this deck looks to apply constant pressure and close out games quickly.

Utilizing Eldrazi creatures and ramp spells, this deck aims to control the game by quickly ramping into powerful Eldrazi threats. The deck includes powerful control cards such as Kozilek's Return and Malevolent Rumble to handle opposing threats, while also using cards like Utopia Sprawl and Eldrazi Temple to accelerate mana production. With finishers like Emrakul, the Promised End and Sire of Seven Deaths, the deck looks to overwhelm the opponent with huge threats and overpowering board presence.

This deck focuses on disrupting the opponent's game plan with a mix of hand disruption, removal spells, and graveyard hate while deploying aggressive creatures to pressure the opponent's life total. The key strategy revolves around using efficient removal spells like Fatal Push and Prismatic Ending to control the board while deploying powerful creatures like Phelia, Exuberant Shepherd and Ketramose, the New Dawn to close out the game quickly. Additionally, using cards like Relic of Progenitus and Ephemerate to disrupt the opponent's graveyard synergies provides another layer of disruption to the game plan.

The deck revolves around assembling a powerful combo using Paradox Engine, Mystic Forge, and Karn, the Great Creator to generate a loop of mana and spells, ultimately winning the game with Ugin, the Eye of the Storms. Various mana ramp artifacts like Astral Cornucopia and Everflowing Chalice help accelerate the combo, while cards like Chalice of the Void and Glaring Fleshraker disrupt opponents' strategies. The deck also includes Eldrazi Temple and Urza's Saga to help find key cards and maintain consistency in executing the combo.
